              "kind": "text",
              "text": "For scalar "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", returns the data type with the smallest size and smallest scalar kind which can hold its value.  For non-scalar array "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", returns the vector's dtype unmodified."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Floating point values are not demoted to integers,\nand complex values are not demoted to floats."
